# Git Workflow Rules

## NEVER push without explicit permission

- NEVER run `git push` unless the user explicitly says "push it", "push", or "push to github"
- Creating a commit does NOT mean you can push
- After committing, always stop and wait for the user to say push

## NEVER include project or token names in commits

- Do NOT mention specific project names (e.g. BNBShare, BORT, Ensoul, etc.) in commit titles or bodies
- Do NOT mention token contract addresses in commit messages
- Do NOT mention specific website domains (e.g. bnbshare.fun, bortagent.xyz) in commit titles
- Keep commits generic and describe the technical change, not the specific project it was tested against

## Commit message format

✅ GOOD:
```
fix: skip form-fill pass when plan already includes fill steps
feat: fallback to project metadata when website scraping is blocked
```

❌ BAD:
```
fix: BNBShare token creation form not submitting
feat: fix BORT claim extraction when bortagent.xyz blocks scraping
```
